1. Moj *talent* za pisanje priča je počeo da se razvija još u detinjstvu. (My *talent* for writing stories began to develop in childhood.)
2. Ona ima neobičan *talent* za pronalaženje jeftinih letova. (She has an unusual *talent* for finding cheap flights.)
3. Većina ljudi misli da je *talent* dovoljan za uspeh, ali istina je da bez napornog rada nećete daleko stići. (Most people think that *talent* is enough for success, but the truth is that without hard work, you won't get far.)
4. Kada sam krenuo na audiciju, nisam ni slutio da imam *talent* za glumu. (When I went to audition, I had no idea that I had *talent* for acting.)
5. Talentovana deca imaju posebne potrebe koje se moraju razumeti i podržati. (*Talented* children have special needs that must be understood and supported.)
6. Bez obzira na to koliko ste talentovani, uvek postoji nešto novo što možete naučiti. (No matter how talented you are, there is always something new you can learn.)